[30;1m3894 | [0m[35m  implementation of `Settings.exists()`, which previously did a shallow[0m
[30;1m3895 | [0m[35m  check of loaded data. It has now been updated to perform a[0m
[30;1m3896 | [0m[35m  `Settings.get()` of the key in question, and compares that to a newly[0m
[30;1m3897 | [0m[35m  defined sentinel value to ensure `None` values do not cause a false[0m
[30;1m3898 | [0m[35m  negative result.[0m
[30;1m3899 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m3640 | [0m[35m    The object merge dutifully tried to expand this item out again and again[0m
[30;1m3641 | [0m[35m    even in the case that the list was a single item, resulting in [item],[0m

[30;1m3643 | [0m[35m    run again, but for each item in the list. In this particular instance[0m
